  "detailed_description": [
    {
      "heading": "Power over Ethernet (PoE) Adapter",
      "text": "The Ubiquiti U-POE-af is a highly functional Power over Ethernet (PoE) adapter, meticulously designed to deliver remote power to Ubiquiti devices compatible with the 802.3af PoE standard. This adapter enables the transmission of power alongside data over a single Ethernet cable, simplifying installations where electrical power accessibility is limited. The U-POE-af by Ubiquiti is tailored to facilitate the deployment of network hardware such as access points, IP cameras, and other network equipment, specifically in environments where minimizing cable clutter is crucial."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Key Features",
      "text": "Features:\n\n- Delivers up to 15W of PoE\n- Compatible with the U6 Mesh, Camera G4 Pro, and other PoE devices\n- Surge, peak pulse, and overcurrent protection\n- AC cable with earth ground\n- LED indicator for status monitoring"
    },
    {
      "heading": "Performance and Compatibility",
      "text": "The adapter supports Gigabit Ethernet, a critical feature for maintaining maximum data throughput and ensuring that the delivery of power does not impede network performance. This capability is vital in environments demanding high-speed data transfer. The U-POE-af adheres to the 802.3af PoE standard, ensuring compatibility with a wide range of devices that also comply with this specification. It delivers up to 15 watts of power, suitable for operating efficient network devices. Moreover, to protect against voltage spikes and improve system reliability, the U-POE-af includes surge protection. This feature is critical for preventing damage to both the PoE adapter and the connected hardware during electrical surges and spikes."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Ease of Use",
      "text": "Designed for ease of use, the U-POE-af is a plug-and-play device, necessitating no software configuration and enabling rapid deployment. This straightforward setup is beneficial for users with varying levels of technical expertise."
    }
  ],
